% references.bib — Academic Research OS
% Project: LLM-Assisted Literature Screening (RQ-001)
%
% Citekey convention: authorYYYYkeyword
%   - author:   first author last name, lowercase, no diacritics (e -> e, u -> u)
%   - YYYY:     4-digit publication year (use arXiv submission year for preprints)
%   - keyword:  single most distinctive content word from title, lowercase
%   - collision: append a, b, c (e.g., smith2024agentsa)
%   Example: smith2024agents, brown2023retrieval, zhang2022survey
%
% Rules:
%   - DO NOT commit PDF files to this repo. Store local paths in papers_manifest.csv.
%   - Every entry must have: author, title, year, doi OR url, abstract, keywords.
%   - Prefer published version over preprint; link arXiv ID via eprint field if both exist.
%   - Verify DOIs resolve before submission; use scripts/check_dois.py.
%
% Better BibTeX (Zotero plugin) configuration:
%   Install: https://retorque.re/zotero-better-bibtex/
%   Recommended key format: [auth:lower][year][title:1:lower]
%   This produces keys matching our convention automatically.
%   Enable "Keep keys stable" to prevent key changes on paper update.
%   Export via: File > Export Library > Better BibTeX > select "Keep updated"

